Songs from the show, cut from the movie:
*Cooties - Amber (Featured on the soundtrack sung by Aimee Allen)
*Mama, I'm a Big Girl Now - Tracy & Edna - Amber & Velma - Penny & Prudy (not in the film, possibility to play during the end credits and will also be featured on the soundtrack sung by Nikki Blonsky, [[Ricki Lake]], and [[Marissa Jaret Winokur]])
*The Madison [dance number] (Replaced by "Ladies' Choice")
*The Legend of Miss Baltimore Crabs (Reprise) 
*The Big Dollhouse - Female Company
*Good Morning Baltimore (Reprise) - Tracy (replaced by the song "I Can Wait", but was cut for being too repetitive.)

*On the [[May 16]]th edition of ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]'', they showed a clip of the movie with The Dynamites singing a song on "The Corny Collins Show"'s ''Negro Day''. The name of the song and whether it will be featured on the soundtrack is currently unknown.

